is more suitable for artificial turf. The reason for this can be explained from three perspectives, one user base, the second is the shoes, the third is the professional level. You know, the hotel and the golf course to face the user base is different, the hotel guests to visit, the majority of meetings, the hotel should even select the artificial turf as the ground. Because the real grass golf course is more delicate, so the usual shoes or sneakers is not suitable, so some golf courses have a mandatory requirement, guests must wear studded golf shoes to allow the end. The hotel even if there are golf courses, it is also used as recreational facilities, so the artificial turf on it.</span>\r\n                </p>\r\n                <p><br/></p>', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 17, 1);
INSERT INTO `cms_html_module` VALUES ('156307635405772986', 'NEWS_DETAIL', 'news_list_20_1', 'news_list_20', '', '', '', '', '\r\n                <p><span style=\"font-size:19px;font-family:&#39;Times New Roman&#39;,&#39;serif&#39;\">Earlier, according to the &quot;Sun&quot; reported that in 2018 World Cup held in Russia, will be arranged in 11 cities in the artificial turf stadium. As we all know, most of the top football matches are played in a well-maintained natural grass court, while Russian football is dominated by artificial turf pitches, which is a challenge to the team that comes to this match.</span>\r\n                </p>\r\n                <p><span style=\"font-size:19px;font-family:&#39;Times New Roman&#39;,&#39;serif&#39;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n                <p><span style=\"font-size:19px;font-family:&#39;Times New Roman&#39;,&#39;serif&#39;\">At the time of the 2015 World Cup of Women&#39;s World Cup in Canada, all of them had used synthetic grass pitches to compete. This caused controversy at that time. This caused great controversy at that time, and the women football players led by the U.S. female star even jointly filed a lawsuit against FIFA and the Canadian Football Association. FIFA pledges not to use artificial grass next time. Litigation was withdrawn.</span>\r\n                </p>\r\n                <p><span style=\"font-size:19px;font-family:&#39;Times New Roman&#39;,&#39;serif&#39;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n                <p><span style=\"font-size:19px;font-family:&#39;Times New Roman&#39;,&#39;serif&#39;\">Artificial turf stadium failed to test for the first time in the World Cup, then the FIFA General Secretary is still full of confidence in the artificial turf, said the future may also be used in the men&#39;s soccer World Cup artificial turf stadium. In fact, the 2018 World Cup from the qualifying team has encountered artificial turf, many teams in order to adapt to the venue also specially in the artificial turf field practice.</span>\r\n                </p>\r\n                <p><span style=\"font-size:19px;font-family:&#39;Times New Roman&#39;,&#39;serif&#39;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n                <p><span style=\"font-size:19px;font-family:&#39;Times New Roman&#39;,&#39;serif&#39;\">Russia, the organizer of the 2018 World Cup, uses artificial grass pitches year-round because of its geographical relationship. For most of the year, it is cold and cold weather, making it very unsuitable for the growth of natural grass. In 2008 for the Champions League final, Luzhniki stadium in Moscow laid a natural grass, but due to improper maintenance, Chelsea captain accidental slippage in the penalty shoot-out, missed the championship.</span>\r\n                </p>\r\n                <p><span style=\"font-size:19px;font-family:&#39;Times New Roman&#39;,&#39;serif&#39;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n                <p><span style=\"font-size:19px;font-family:&#39;Times New Roman&#39;,&#39;serif&#39;\">The majority of football players who enter the World Cup come from strong football clubs, who often spare no effort to prepare their players for a good, quality natural turf course. For those who have adapted to play in these venues, artificial turf is really a big test. To this end, Russia uses a different from the new technology, that is, a mixture of artificial grass and natural grass turf, and strive to achieve the best sports experience.</span>\r\n                </p>\r\n                <p><span style=\"font-size:19px;font-family:&#39;Times New Roman&#39;,&#39;serif&#39;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n                <p><span style=\"font-size:19px;font-family:&#39;Times New Roman&#39;,&#39;serif&#39;\">Artificial turf development so far, through continuous improvement and innovation, from the playground in primary and secondary schools to the street stadium, to rental venues and stadiums, from ordinary courses to professional golf courses, and finally finally set foot in the World Cup, the world&#39;s highest level 